Xu became openly involved in the China Democracy Party in November.
During Clinton's visit to China in June, Wang announced the formation of the China Democracy Party.
Beijing police Sunday detained one of Xu's China Democracy Party colleagues, Zha Jianguo, to prevent him from attending the trial, Xu's wife said.
Chinese courts sentenced dissidents Xu Wenli and Wang Youcai to 13 and 11 years for trying to organize an opposition political party.
Security forces have orchestrated a concerted crackdown, trampling China's slim legal safeguards to crush the China Democracy Party.
Police have sporadically detained supporters of the democracy party.
